race.comment: SAVAII (4) seeks the hat-trick for a top Sydney stable. He was a big CL1 winner here last time and will be fitter again. He has early speed and Collett stays aboard. Promising and should be winning again. KENDALIA (8) won a Gosford Maiden three back and has been close up at the provincials since. He's switched from Joe Pride to Matt Dale on a 27-day return and can threaten with average luck in the run. Sydney-trained GREYGENTA (7) brings a win and narrow defeat from Kembla Grange and this is a touch easier. Dropping back 200m off a brief freshen won't prove an issue and she's also a chance. ROCCO LINI (12) needs to find more to be winning but the local is heading in the right direction and will be around the mark.
